    <h2>Initial Results</h2>
    <p>
      Our initial algorithm attempt was not very successful. The Harris corner detector was somewhat successful in differentiating forks from knives and spoons. This can be seen in the following image of all three utensil types with a corresponding image of Harris corner scores. The points on the fork spokes are clearly local maxima. 
    </p>
    <p>
      However, the above image also demonstrates the main issue with the Harris corner detection method. Namely, the Harris corner detection algorithm is quite sensitive and easily confused by reflections or any texture on the utensils.
    </p>
    <p>
      The issue with the Hough transform was that it required very good edge detection, which was difficult to ensure. Furthermore, for reasonably large images and a variable estimated ellipse size, the transform took too long to run.
